packageMeta.name: purescript-orders
packageMeta.description: A handful of utility `newtype`s for the `Ord` type class.

declarations.comments:
A newtype wrapper which provides a reversed `Ord` instance. For example:

    sortBy (comparing Down) [1,2,3] = [3,2,1]
declarations.title: Down

declarations.comments:
Provides a `Semigroup` based on the `max` function. If the type has a
`Bounded` instance, then a `Monoid` instance is provided too. For example:

    unwrap (Max 5 <> Max 6) = 6
    mempty :: Max Ordering = Max LT
declarations.title: Max

declarations.comments:
Provides a `Semigroup` based on the `min` function. If the type has a
`Bounded` instance, then a `Monoid` instance is provided too. For example:

    unwrap (Min 5 <> Min 6) = 5
    mempty :: Min Ordering = Min GT
declarations.title: Min
